  "prompt": "If I live in NYC but work on Long Island do I have to pay city income tax?",
  "response": "Yes, if you live in New York City, you are subject to the New York City income tax, regardless of where you work. This means that even if you work on Long Island, as a resident of NYC, you will still have to pay the city's income tax. The tax is based on your entire income, not just the income earned within the city. However, you may be able to claim a credit for any taxes paid to another jurisdiction, which can help alleviate some of the tax burden. It's always a good idea to consult with a tax professional for personalized advice based on your specific situation.",
